lead_paragraph: The Berlin radio, quoting a Japanese Army spokesman at Hankow, said yesterday that two planes attacked the region of Hankow and Wuchang, according to The Associated Press. The Axis version was that three bombs fell on Wuchang, across the Yangtze from Hankow, setting two thatched Chinese houses afire and collapsing a third.
